Swiss Regulator Says Splitting Biggest Banks Not on the Table

-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l   a n d   D y l a n   G r i f f i t h s
-- 
2011-09-26T09:39:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/swiss-regulator-says-splitting-biggest-banks-not-on-the-table.html
Switzerland ’s financial regulator
said splitting off the investment-banking businesses of the
country’s biggest banks, UBS AG and  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) ,
isn’t currently “on the table.”  Anne Heritier Lachat, chair of the board of directors of
the Swiss Financial Market Supervisory Authority, or Finma,
commented today at a conference in Zurich.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dylan Griffiths at 
 dgriffiths1@bloomberg.net  